Troubleshooting

ProblemSolution
Pictures are mottled.Shutter speed is slow and the ambient temperature is high: This is normal and does not indicate a malfunction. Use pixel mapping ( ≡ 117). * X-rays, cosmic rays, and other forms of radiation interacting with the image sensor may cause bright spots of various col- ors such as white, red, and blue. Pixel mapping helps reduce the occurrence of such bright spots. The camera has been used continuously at high temperatures: Turn the camera off and wait for it to cool down (□□ 35, 327). A temperature warning is displayed: Turn the camera off and wait for it to cool down (□□ 35, 327).
